members.name: DOMRectReadOnly()
members.description: Defined to create a new DOMRectReadOnly object, but note that this constructor cannot be called by 3rd party JavaScript: doing so returns an "Illegal constructor" typeError.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: The x coordinate of the DOMRectReadOnly's origin.

parameters.name: y
parameters.description: The y coordinate of the DOMRectReadOnly's origin.

members.name: DOMRectReadOnly.x
members.description: The x coordinate of the DOMRect's origin.

members.name: DOMRectReadOnly.y
members.description: The y coordinate of the DOMRect's origin.

members.name: DOMRectReadOnly.top
members.description: Returns the top coordinate value of the DOMRect (usually the same as y.)

members.name: DOMRectReadOnly.right
members.description: Returns the right coordinate value of the DOMRect (usually the same as x + width).

members.name: DOMRectReadOnly.bottom
members.description: Returns the bottom coordinate value of the DOMRect (usually the same as y + height).

members.name: DOMRectReadOnly.left
members.description: Returns the left coordinate value of the DOMRect (usually the same as x).

members.name: DOMRectReadOnly.fromRect()
members.description: Creates a new DOMRect object with a given location and dimensions.

parameters.name: rectangle Optional
